	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64515359"><p>I think this is an A+ effort to team up the community with the police. We should definitely start doing everything we can to help these dirtbags get caught.</p><p>However, there is no mention of how the police were able to get a search warrant. What questions did they ask to establish that the owner was legit? How long did it take to get the warrant? Who did the owner talk to? Was the owner present at the search? This is something we all need to replicate to make this technique work. The police obviously need to conduct the search, citizens should never confront possible criminals on their own.</p><p>Note that in this case no suspects have been caught yet. There are hundreds, possibly thousands, of victims. If you haven't put your name on your tools or tagged them in some way, it's probably pretty unlikely you'll be able to recover your stolen goods without a lot of work.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64515359">
<span class="ind"></span><a id="reply_link_64515359" class="btn link" href="//yro.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23342271&amp;op=Reply&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;pid=64515359" onclick="D2.replyTo(64515359); return false;">Reply to This</a> 	<a href="#" class="comment_share_toggle btn link">Share</a>
